data.database_description: This database is designed to manage educational and contact information for students, candidates, and general individuals within an organization. It includes detailed tables for storing addresses, personal details of people, course offerings, student registrations, attendance records, candidate profiles, and assessments. The schema facilitates the linking of individuals to their respective physical locations through address records and manages relationships between students and courses via registration and attendance tracking. Additionally, it supports the assessment process for candidates by connecting them with their evaluation outcomes, illustrating a comprehensive system for educational administration and personal data management.

columns.columnDescription: Primary key uniquely identifying each address record.
First line of the address, typically street name and number.
Second line of the address, such as suite or apartment number.
Name of the city where the address is located.
Postal code for the address location.
State, province, or county associated with the address.
Country where the address is located.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each person.
The first name of the individual.
The middle name of the individual, if applicable.
The last name of the individual.
Contact number for mobile communication with the individual.
Email address for electronic correspondence with the individual.
Username used by the individual to access systems or services.
Encrypted password associated with the login name for system access.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each student, referencing a person.
Additional descriptive information about the student.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Manages student profiles, linking them to personal details in the People table.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each course.
Name of the course.
Detailed description of the course content.
Additional information related to the course.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about various courses offered.

columns.columnDescription: Primary key uniquely identifying each person-address association.
Foreign key referencing the unique identifier of a person in the People table.
Foreign key referencing the unique identifier of an address in the Addresses table.
Start date and time for when the address association is valid for the person.
End date and time for when the address association is valid for the person.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Links individuals to their addresses along with valid date ranges for those associations.

columns.columnDescription: Identifier for the registered student, linked to their profile.
Identifier for the course being taken, linked to its details.
Date and time when the registration was made.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Maintains records of student registrations for courses.

columns.columnDescription: Identifier for the attending student, linked to their registration.
Identifier for the course attended, linked to its details.
Date and time when attendance was recorded.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Tracks student attendance for specific courses on given dates.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each candidate.
Additional information about the candidate, such as name.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Contains personal details and identifiers for candidates within the organization.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier linking to a specific candidate.
The qualification level or type that the candidate is being assessed for.
Timestamp indicating when the assessment took place.
Code representing the result of the assessment (e.g., Pass, Fail).

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores assessment records for candidates, including qualification details and outcomes.
